Commentary: FOUR! Straightaway off the mark! And in some fashion! Slightly overpitched outside off, Islam leans into it and then drives it through covers for the first boundary.
Again it is pitched fuller and outside off, Islam this time lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Length and around off, Islam comes on the front foot and taps it on the off side.
Full and sliding down leg, Islam clips it towards fine leg and crosses ends for a single.
Short of good length from Roach, Tamim goes onto his toes and pushes the ball to gully.
A full offered and Tamim misses out as he strokes it straight to mid off. End of the first over.
Full and down leg, Islam looks to clip it to the leg side but he misses it as the keeper Joshua Da Silva takes it by going low to his right.
Fuller on middle, Islam clips it straight to mid-wicket this time.
FOUR! Easy pickings! A low full toss on the pads, Shadman Islam just clips it past mid-wicket and the ball races to the fence quickly. Gabriel is struggling to land the ball in right areas.
Short of good length on middle, Islam hops and tucks it to the leg side.
Another delivery that is bowled in line with the leg stump and Shadman turns it away to the leg side once again.
Fuller and on leg, Islam clips it past the man at short leg and takes a couple on offer.
Fuller and around off, Tamim is well forward as he blocks this one out.
Length and outside off, Tamim does well to keep his bat close to his body and then lets the ball go through to the keeper.
FOUR! That's where Tamim likes! Pitched up a bit wide and Iqbal leans into the drive and creams it through covers for his first boundary. That should give hi m confidence.
Length and on off, Iqbal defends it off the inner half of the bat by coming onto the front foot.
Good length and around off, tapped towards point this time.
Length and on off, Tamim does well to defend it out off the front foot and onto the pitch this time.
Full and on  the leg stump, Shadman clips it all along the ground towards fine leg and gets a single this time.
FOUR! Nicely done! Gabriel coming from round the wicket to Iqbal bowls a fuller length ball down leg and Tamim flicks it off his pads as the ball races to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Length and around off, Tamim blocks it to the leg isde this time off the front foot.
On a fuller length and on middle, Tamim tucks it off the front foot towards short leg.
Fuller and on the pads once again from Shanon. Tamim  clips it through mid-wicket for a single. He also becomes the leading run scorer for Bangladesh in Tests overtaking Rahim.
Full and around off, Islam leans into the stroke as he hits it through mid off. The ball goes to long off as the batsmen take a couple of runs.
Fuller and in line with the off pole, Tamim does well to come on the front foot and then push it to mid on.
A bumper from Roach as Tamim sits under it without any fuss.

OUT! DRAGGED ON! Roach is elated and West Indies are celebrating! Lovely bowling that from Kemar. Bowls it on a length and around off, Tamim comes on the front foot to play at that but the ball just about gains the inward movement and takes the inside edge before disturbing the woodwork behind.
A bumper to welcome the new batsman. Najmul though sits under it.
Fuller and on off, Hossain Shanto defends it to the off side.
A length ball on off, Najmul drives it to covers. A successful over from Roach comes to an end. A wicket maiden too.
A short one from Gabriel and Islam can only duck under it.
A back of a length ball on middle and leg, Islam hops and pushes it away from short leg.
Another one banged in short from Gabriel and Islam ducks under it.
Another short one and Islam does not offer as stroke to it.
Another back of a length ball but it does not rise as expected and Islam does well to drops it off his gloves to the gully with soft hands though.
Length ball on middle and leg, Islam is right behind the line of the ball as he blocks it out.
FOUR! Glorious hit! Full and in the slot for Hossain Shanto as he drives it through covers and beats the dive od the man at mid off. The ball races the fence for a boundary at long off.
Length and around off, Najmul defends it off the front foot towards covers.
Good length around middle, Hossain Shanto defends it once again off the front foot.
Another fuller one from Roach but Najmul this time plays it straight to covers.
Length and around off, Hossain Shanto plays it off the back foot towards the bowler.
Fuller around off, Najmul is happy to play it to mid off this time.
Gabriel persists with  the leg stumpish line and Islam clips it towards fine leg for a single.
Full and down leg, Najmul misses his flick as Joshua Da Silva takes it by going to his right.
Length and around leg, Hossain Shanto clips it past short leg and through mid-wicket for a single.
Slightly fuller and on middle, Islam does well to defend it off the back foot towards point. He though made sure to keep his bottom hand loose there so the ball will go all along the ground.

BEATEN! That is a lovely delivery from Gabriel! Bowls a length ball around middle and off, Islam who is waiting on the back foot to defend is caught by surprise with the slight away movement as the ball goes past the outside edge.
Full and targetting the base of middle stump, Islam pushes it to mid-wicket off the back foot to see off the over.
Tossed up around off, Shanto is beaten on the outside edge as he looks to defend it. A great start for the giant man there.
Floated on off, watchfully played out by Najmul.
Floated around off, Najmul does well to play it past gully for a single.
Tossed up around off,m pushed to covers.
On off, Islam defends it to mid off.
Flighted around off, Shadman solidly blocks it off the front foot. End of a good first over for Cornwall.
Full and down leg, najmul misses his clip there. The keeper takes it behind the sticks.
FOUR! Lovely hit! Full and in the slot for Hossain Shanto. Najmul plays it with a straight bat and drives it all along the ground as the ball meets the ropes at long off.
Goes back to bowling a length ball around off, Najmul does well to blocks it out to the off side.
Length and across the southpaw, Hossain Shanto drops his wrists and lets the ball go through to the keeper.
Length and angled on off, Najmul hops and pushes it to covers.

BEATEN! Excellent length! That is the area Gabriel should bowl consistently at. A length ball in the channel around off, Hossain Shanto pushes at it without any footwork but gets beaten on the outside edge.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
FOUR! Elegantly played! Tossed up around middle and off, Islam goes deep iside his crease before flicking it away through mid on for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, pushed to covers.
Flatter and on off, played down to short third man this time.
Flighted around off, Islam does well to keep it out.
And once again Islam is solid in defense to this tossed up ball.
Length and around off, blocked away by Najmul this time.
Another short of good length and on off, Shanto defends it off the back foot now.
Another shortish length ball on off, Najmul blocks it right under his eyes off the back foot.
Length and outside off, Najmul lets it be.
Length and on leg, Najmul clips it through to square leg and takes a couple of runs this time.
Short and on midlde, played towards the off side by Najmul.
Tossed up on off, defended to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up and slower on middle, pushed to short mid-wicket once again.
Fuller and on off, driven through mid off for a single this time.
On off, Najmul rightly blocks it off the front foot.
On middle and leg, clipped through mid-wicket for a single.
Another floated ball on middle, clipped towards the leg side this time.
Length and on off, pushed to the off side.
Length and around off, defended to the off side off the front foot.
Good length and outside off, left alone by Najmul.
Fuller and around off, Hossain Shanto does well to defend it off the front foot towards covers.
Length and around off, Hossain Shanto does well to hop and defend it off the back foot towards mid off.
Length and around off, Hossain Shanto pushes it off the back foot towards mid off.
Fuller and on middle, turned towards short mid-wicket.
Fuller once again but on off this time and Islam does well to drive it to long off for a single.
On middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated on leg, tucked towards square leg for a single.
Full and on off, pushed down to mid on this time by Islam.
Fuller and on off, driven towards mid off this time by Shadman.
Length and around the hips of Najmul, Hossain Shanto clips it through backward square leg for a single.
Fuller and on middle, clipped towards deep backward square leg once again by  Isalm for a single.
Another leg side delivery and Najmul clips it to mid-wicket.
And once again on middle and leg, blocked out off the back foot towards mid-wicket by Hossain Shanto.
This time slightly fuller and on middle, Shanto defends it off the front foot.
A back of a length ball on middle, Hossain Shanto does well to get right behind the ball to play at it. A good first over for the debutant Mayers.
Tossed up on off, kept out.
Fuller on off, Islam dead bats it to the off side.
Floated on off, Islam defend its it past the silly mid off fielder.
Flighted around off, pushed to mid off.
Floated and on off and middle, Islam dead bats it onto the track.
Loopy outside off, Shadman drives it through covers and gets a brace as the ball does not go to the fence due to the lack of pace.
Full and angled around off, Najmul defends it out.
Length and on middle and leg, turned out to the leg side by Hossain Shanto once again.
Once again the middle stump line from Mayers continues as Najmul flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full and on leg, tucked past mid-wicket for a brace. 50-up for Bangladesh.
Full and on leg, Shanto turns it towards square leg and scampers for a single.
On off this time from Mayers as Islam blocks it out to mid off.
Tossed up on off, pushed away to the off side by Shanto.
Full and on leg, swept away down to deep square leg for a single.
Floated on off, kept out.
Lovely bowling! Quicker and tossed up outside off, Islam looks to push it from within the crease but is beaten on the outside edge this time.
Floated around middle and leg, turned away towards square leg for a single.
Once again it is on the pads and Islam does well to clip it off his pads towards the leg side for a single.
Length and down leg, Islam misses his flick this time though.
Once again the line is down leg and Islam clips it to short mid-wicket this time.
Full and on off, driven down to long on for a single.
Full and outside off, Najmul defends it to the off side off the front foot.
Length and around off, blocked out this time by Najmul.
Another length ball on off, Shanto does well to keep it out without any fuss.
FOUR! A freebie! Flatter and outside off, Shadman Islam rocks on the back foot and then cuts it in front of point for a boundary.
Gets back to his normal line of bowling around off, Islam does well to defend it.
On off, pushed to the close in fielder.

Lovely bowling! Tossed up and a bit of air there as Islam looks to poke at it but is beaten all ends up. The keeper and the close in fielders get excited with the ball doing something off the surface.
Full on off, driven through to covers for a single.
On middle and leg, swept away towards square leg for a couple of runs.
Length and around off, Islam does well to defend it out to the off side.
Full and on middle, Islam pushes it to mid on now.
Good length and outside off, Islam does not offer a stroke this time.
Full and on off, driven down the ground the bowler fields in his followthrough.
Short of good length around off, punched off the back foot towards point now.
Mayers further pitches it up n middle, Islam clips it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Shanto defends it out to the off side.
Tossed up on off, pushed to the off side once gain.
Flatter around off, kept out off the back foot.
Floated on middle, kept out safely by Shanto.
FOUR! Swept away! Full and around off, Shanto gets down on his knees and sweeps it through to deep square leg for a boundary.
On off, kept out to covers.

OUT! RUN OUT! Poor mix up and a very sad and anticlimactic end to what was looking like a great stand. The West Indies players are enjoying while Najmul Hossain Shanto trudges off in sadness and disappointment. On the pads, Shadman Islam flicks it towards backward square leg. Roach goes to his left and gets to the ball. Shadman wants two but Najmul Hossain Shanto is stuck to his crease. Shadman is almost at the other end and Shanto decides to go for it. The throw is at the keeper's end. Da Silva removes his gloves and sends a good throw to Mayers who does the rest. Najmul Hossain Shanto is well short of his crease and has to walk back.
Fuller on off, Shadman keeps it out.
Around off, Shadman defends it.
Full around off, Shadman pushes it to cover.
Good length delivery on off, Shadman keeps it out.
On the stumps, Shadman keeps it out. End of an eventful over from Mayers.
Tossed up on off, pushed out to covers by Haque.
Another floated ball on off, Haque keeps it out to the off side once again.
Floated outside off, defended solidly by Haque.
On off, pushed to the off side.
Floated on middle, Haque played it to mid on.
Floated on off, defended out by Haque safely.
Gabriel comes around the wicket and bowls one full outside off. Asking Shadman to drive but he is not interested.
Good ball! Good length delivery pitching outside off and coming back in with the angle. Shadman has a poke at it but misses. Lucky not to edge it.
Very full around off, Shadman jams it out as he defends it to cover.
Length ball on off, kept out by Shadman.
Yorker length on off, Shadman defends it.
Low full toss on off and middle. Shadman pushes it to mid off.
Floated on middle, Mominul keeps it out.
Tossed up on the stumps, Mominul bends his back and blocks it.
Flighted around off, Mominul pushes it to cover.
Mominul is off the mark! On the pads, the Bangladesh Test skipper turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Flighted on off and middle, Shadman keeps it out.
Short and spinning away outside off, Shadman cuts it but straight to point.
Outside off, Mominul lets it carry to the keeper.
Low full toss on middle, Mominul strokes it to mid on. Gabriel is bowling too full in ths spell. Needs to pull back his length.

NOT OUT! The ball clearly bounced in front of square leg and Mominul survives. Shortish ball on the pads, Mominul looks to tuck it but does so uppishly. The fielder at short leg holds onto the ball and appeals. The umpires get together and send it upstairs with the soft signal as NOT OUT. Replays roll in and they show the ball clearly bounced in front of the fielder.
On middle, Mominul defends it.

Gabriel almost gets the better of Mominul once again. Gabriel dishes a pacy short ball on the body. Mominul looks to get it away on the leg side but the ball keeps high and hits him on his glove. It lobs and falls just in front of short leg. Had the fielder there been more squarer, it might have carried.
Shortish ball around off, Mominul keeps it out.
Floated on middle and off, Shadman keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Shadman keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, Shadman strokes it through mid on for one.
Floated on off, Mominul defends it off the inner half of his bat.
Pitched outside off and turning away. Mominul looks to cut but misses. The ball hits the keeper's glove and falls just away from first slip. Does not cost any run.
Flighted on middle, Mominul strokes it to long on and keeps the strike. That will be Lunch on Day 1!
On a length and around off from round the wicket from Gabriel. Haque does well to defend it out off the front foot though.
Length and around off, Haque once again keeps it out safely this time from within the crease.
Full and on middle, Mominul does well to tuck it to the man at mid-wicket.
A slightly short of good length delivery. It bounces a tad extra as Haque keeps his bat close to him and lets the ball pass through to the keeper.

FIVE WIDES! That was wayward! What was Gabriel thinking there. Tries to bowl a ball that is angled onto the pads of Haque but ends up dishing out a wide one down leg. The keeper dives to his right but cannot stop it as the ball goes to the fine leg fence. Wide given.
Length and on the pads, clipped away towards square leg for a single.
On middle, turned to the leg side for a dot.
Full and around off, driven straight down the ground by Haque but Roach does well to go low and field the ball in his followthrough.
A half volley from Roach and Haque drives it through covers. Though the timing is not there on the ball to reach the fence as the batsmen settle for a couple there.
Good length and around off, pushed to mid off now.
Fuller on off, Haque comes on the front foot to defend but the ball takes the inner half of the bat and goes towards mid-wicket.
Length and going down leg, Haque clips it towards deep square leg for a couple once again.
Length and around off, punched straight to straightish mid off.
Full on off, punched down to mid on from Islam.
Pitched up a bit fuller and outside off, Islam watches the ball and then lifts his willow for the ball to pass to the keeper.
On a length and on leg, Islam turns it away quickly past short leg and gets a single as the ball goes to deep square leg region.
Short of length and around off, Haque hops inside his crease and taps it to the off side this time around.
Another short of good length ball, Haque gets onto his toes and keeps it ball onto the pitch off the back foot.
Length and down leg, Mominul goes for the flick but is beaten there as the keeper takes it by going to his right.
Full and on off, driven to short cover now.
Full and around off, pushed down to mid off by Islam.
Slower and fuller on middle, pushed down to short cover once again.
Short of good length on middle, pushed off the back foot towards the bowler once again.
Another length ball around off, Islam manages to defend it off the back foot solidly.
Edgy but safe! Length and angled into middle, Islam looks to clip it to the leg side but the ball goes to gully off the leading edge. But luckily the ball goes all along the ground.
Short of good length on middle, Haque hops and defends it to short leg.
Length  and on middle and off, punched down to mid on off the back foot.
FOUR! Handsomely done! Short and width offered outside off, Haque stands tall and cuts it through backward point for a boundary.
Fuller and around middle, pushed off the back foot towards mid on.
Length and outside off, pushed to covers this time.
No run, that is defended solidly off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Islam dead bats it off the front foot.
Another floater on off, pushed down the track.
Flighted on off, pushed to the off side.
Fuller and on middle, clipped towards mid-wicket.
kept out by Islam.
Flatter outside off, Islam pushes it to covers.
Length and outside off, Haque lets the ball through to the keeper.
Fuller on off, Mominul drives but the ball is intercepted by short cover.
Length and on off, pushed off the back foot towards short cover once again.
Fuller and around off, driven straight to short cover.
On a fuller length and on off, pushed to mid off now.
Length and outside off, Haque watches the ball and makes a leave this time.
Fuller outside off, Islam goes for the slog down the ground but ends up chipping it towards mid on.
Tossed up on off, pushed back to the bowler now.
Full and on middle, driven down to long on for a single.
On middle and leg, Haque tucks it to the leg side for a single.
Fuller on off, driven back to the bowler.
Nice loopy delivery around off, Islam comes on the front foot and defends it.
Short of good length and outside off, Haque drops his wrists and lets the ball go through.
Full and overpitched around off, Haque plays a free-flowing drive but cannot get it past the cover fielder.
Short of good length around off, kept out to the off side now.
Slightly fuller this time and Haque plays it from within the crease as he pushes it down the track.
Length and on the pads, Haque goes to flick it to the leg side but the ball goes off his pads this time.
Full and on middle, Haque drives it down the track towards long on and comes back for the second as the fielder does well to keep the ball in play.
Fuller on middle and off, turned to short leg.
Tossed up on off, Islam plays it from within the crease.
Loopy delivery on off, Islam now comes on the front foot and defends it out.
Flatter and around off, whipped away towards mid-wicket by Islam for a single.
Floated on middle, pushed to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up around off, Haque skips down the track and strokes it towards long on for a single.
Fuller and around off, Haque is right behind the line of the ball as he defends it to short cover.
Slower and fuller on middle, Haque clips it to square leg.
On a length and around off, punched straight to short cover by Mominul.
Slightly overpitched outside off, Haque drives it towards covers for a run this time.
Short of good length on off, Islam taps it to point off the back foot.
Fuller and around off, Islam comes on the front foot and defends it off the inner half of the bat towards the leg side.
Full and on middle, Haque uses his feet and plays it to long on for a single.
On midlde, Islam keeps it out right under his eyes.
Floated around middle, pushed to short mid-wicket this time.
Tossed up around off and midlde, Islam plays it out softly towards short leg.
Fuller on middle, pushed down to mid on now.
No run, the batsman has just watchfully blocked this out.
Full and around off, pushed down to mid-wicket.
Length and around leg, tucked off the hips by Haque towards square leg.
A slightly fuller in length and Haque punches it to mid off now.
Length and around off, Mominul looks to play it straight down the ground but ends up playing it to the man at mid off.
Length and on off, defended solidly off the front foot.
Length and into the pads once again as Haque plays it to square leg.
A rank long hop from Warican, Islam pulls it towards deep mid-wicket where it falls short of the fielder there. A run taken.
Flatter once again on middle, turned towards square leg.
Full on middle, clipped to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on middle, turned towards square leg by Haque off the back foot.
Fuller on middle, clipped off the front foot towards square leg once again.
On off, kept out to the bowler.
FOUR! Short and asking for trouble! Short and on middle, it sits perfectly for Islam to pull it towards deep mid-wicket and fetch a boundary.
Fuller around off, tapped to the off side off the front foot now.
Length and around middle and leg, turned away off the hips towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! Whipped away! Full and on the pads, no issues for Haque as he picks it up and sends it towards deep square leg for a boundary. 100 comes up for Bangladesh.
Length and on off, pushed off the back foot for no runs.
Short of good length on middle, punched down to the leg side by Haque.
Flatter around off, Shadman cuts it through point and gets a couple as the fielder cleans it up before the ropes.
Tossed up on off, Shadman blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Shadman pushes it to mid off.
Flighted on off, kept out by Shadman.
Floated on off, Shadman keeps it out.
Floated on middle, Shadman plays it to mid on.
Flighted on off, Mominul keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, Mominul pushes it to mid on.
Floated on off, Mominul defends it.
Darted on middle, Mominul keeps it out.
This time Mominul strokes it wide of mid on for a run.
Flighted on off, Shadman taps it away from cover for a single and keeps the strike.
On the pads, Shadman flicks it to the leg side for a single.
Floated on off, Mominul defends it.
Tossed up on off, Mominul blocks it.
Floated on off, Mominul pushes it to cover.
Floated on off, Mominul comes down the track and chips it over extra cover for a couple.
Darted on the pads, Mominul flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted on off, Shadman pushes it to cover for a single.
Floated on off, Mominul keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Mominul pushes it to cover.
On the stumps, kept out.
Flatter on off, Haque pushes it to point.
On off, Mominul defends it.

FOUR! Driven away beautifully! Flighted around off, Shadman gets on his front foot and drives it through cover for a boundary. 50-up for Shadman Islam. A well made half ton and he would look to continue the good work and get to a 3-figure mark.
Now smartly taps this to cover and gets a single.
Tossed up on middle, Mominul keeps it out at mid on.
On the pads, Mominul flicks it to mid-wicket.
On middle, Shadman pushes it to mid on.
On the pads, Shadman flicks it to square leg and gets a couple.
Flighted on off, Mominul blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Mominul milks it to long off and gets to the other end.
Appeal for LBW but turned down. Looked to be going down leg. Darted on the pads, Shadman looks to defend but misses. He gets hit on the pad, a hopeful appeal follows but the umpire is unmoved.
On middle and leg, kept out by Shadman.
Flighted on off, Shadman keepsm it out.
Short around off, Shadman defends it with a horizontol bat.
Darted on the pad, Mominul tucks it to the leg side.
Flighted on off, Mominul defends it.
On the stumps, kept out.
Shorter on off, Mominul defends it off his back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Excellent catch from John Campbell and that ends the partnership and sends the Bangladesh skipper back to the pavillion. Floated delivery on middle and leg. It is bowled a tad slower. Mominul looks to flick and does so but he does it uppishly. It goes straight to the man at short mid-wicket. John Campbell there shows great reflex, juggles but takes a good catch.
Floated on middle, Mushfiqur defends it with a straight bat to begin his innings and see off Warrican.
Good length ball around off, Shadman taps it to backward point for a single.
Mushfiqur gets off the mark. On the pads, Rahim flicks it to backward square leg for a single.
Full around off, Shadman drives it through cover and gets a single.
Good length ball around off, Rahim pushes it to cover.
Fuller around off, Rahim gets on his front foot and looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller around off, Rahim flicks it to short mid-wicket.
Floated on middle and leg, Shadman keeps it out.
On the pads, Shadman flicks it to square leg.
On the pads. Shadman flicks it on the leg side.
On off, Islam keeps it out.
NO BALL! Criminal from Jomel Warrican! He oversteps and gets caught by the T.V. umpire. It is on off, Shadman defends it.
Floated on off, Islam defends it.
On the stumps, Shadman keeps it out.
Full and on off, Rahim taps it towards mid on and takes a quick single.
Short and wide outside off, Shadman goes for the cut but ends up hitting it to the man at short cover.
Fuller and on off, driven straight to covers once again by Shadman.
Full and outside off, shadman goes for the drive but his one hand comes off the handle as the ball goes past the outside edge too.
Fuller and outside off, pushed through to covers for a single.
Fuller and on off, punched through covers for a single as the fielder at mid off does well to field it.
Floated on off, pushed to silly point.
Tossed up on middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Floated on off, pushed to point now.
Full and on middle and leg, swept away towards square leg for a single.
Fuller and around off, Shadman goes for the sweep but the ball goes to the square leg fielder who half stops it. A run added.
Tossed up outside leg, Rahim tucks it to the leg side. Warrican has over stepped and it is a No Ball!
FOUR! Pounced onto it! Flatter and outside off, Rahim cuts it in front of point for a boundary.
Length and across the southpaw, Shadman makes a leave this time.
Full and on off, tapped towards the off side.
Short and outside off, Shadman cuts it through backward point for a single.
Fuller and around off, Rahim is rightly on the front foot to defend it safely.
Short of good length and around off, Rahim punches it to the cover-point fielder and yells 'No' to his partner.
Fuller and outside off, Rahim goes for the drive but inside edges it towards mid-wicket. Lucky for him the ball did not end up on the stumps.
Fuller on off, Shadman drives but does not get it past the cover fielder once again.

OUT! LBW! Warrican strikes! West Indies once again coming back into the game. Nice looped up delivery around middle and off, Shadman goes for the sweep but misses it to get rapped on the pads. There is an appeal from the West Indies players and the umpire raises his finger. Shadman departs without reviewing. Replays later show had Shadman reviewed it he would have been saved as the ball was spinning down leg and missing the stumps by a quite margin.
Floated on leg, Shakib tries to tickle it fine but misses it. The keeper to fails to collect it. The ball goes to the fine leg region. The batsmen get two byes.
Floated on middle, Al Hasan clips it to square leg.
On off, pushed down to mid on.
Tossed up on leg, tucked to fine leg for a couple of runs to get off the mark.
Full and on the pads, clipped away towards deep backward square leg for a single.
On off, defended off the front foot by Al Hasan.
Length and around off, pushed to point.
On the pads, Shakib turns it to square leg for a single.
On the pads, Mushfiqur tucks it to mid-wicket and shouts a loud no.
Fuller ball around off, Mushfiqur defends it with a straight bat. That will be TEA on Day 1!

Length and outside off, Shadman makes a leave. Hang on! Roach has overstepped! No Ball called.
Fuller and outside off, Shadman lifts his bat and lets the ball through to the keeper.
Another outside off delivery and Islam does not play at it.
Once again the line is outside off amd Shadman does not have issue to leave it.

OUT! LBW! THREE REDS! Tamim departs for a duck and Cornwall celebrates. He tosses it up perfectly towards off, Tamim looks to play for the turn as he prods forward to defend. The ball though straighten to hit him on the pads. Rakheem Cornwall appeals and up goes the finger. Tamim takes the review. The replays roll in and there is a flat line on Ultra Edge as the Ball Tracker comes on. Three Reds and Tamim Iqbal fails once again.
Fuller and outside off, pushed towards the cover region.

OUT! TAKEN! Another one goes. Second in the over! Lovely from Cornwall. No need to play at such deliveries but Najmul plays at it and pays the price by throwing his wicket away. Nice loopy delivery outside off, Hossain Shanto prods forward and looks to reach for the ball. He though fails to get to the pitch of the ball as it takes the outside edge and goes to the man at first slip where Jermaine Blackwood takes a sharp catch.
Good length ball angled in from around off, Shdman blocks it on the leg side.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Gets closer to the off pole on a length, kept out.
Good length and on middle, pushed towards mid on.
Length delivery around off, blocked.
A solid block again from Shadman. Another length ball just outside off, Shadman comes on the front foot and blocks solidly.
Floated on middle, Mominul looks to defend but the ball takes the inner half and goes to square leg. Haque is up and running.
On middle, played back to the bowler.

A single and Shadman is off the mark on the 29th ball. Floated around middle, Shadman looks to defend but the ball spins in. It takes the inside edge and goes towards the leg side. They cross for one.

Too full and too wide. Haque drives it wide of sweeper cover and takes two.

Kept bowling it short and troubled the batters. He bangs it short again. It is on middle and leg, Shadman looks to fend it off on the leg side but ends up getting a nick behind. Joshua Da Silva makes no mistake. Shadman's stay in the middle it over. Replays later roll in and they show that it came off the gloves. Bangladesh lead by 204.
